    "In other initiatives, the FUTURE-AI consortium [32], comprising 117 international and inter-disciplinary data science and medical experts from 50 countries, delivered the first structured and holistic guideline for trustworthy and ethical AI in healthcare, covering the entire lifecycle of AI.According to the findings of the present study, it was evidenced that out of a total of 381 articles analyzed, about two Notes in Computer Science stand out.",
    "A significant contribution in the field of AI in orthodontics derived also from journals not specialized in dentistry and orthodontics, since high centralities in different WoS categories related to electronic and informatic engineering, computer science, and medical imaging were observed.",
    "These results should not be surprising because AI applications on humans are characterized by a multidisciplinary interest that crosses the medical and computer science scientific community.",
    "In fact, recent attempts to promote standardised and comprehensive reporting of AI tool development and evaluation in 1 3neural networks to evaluate and interpret data, has accelerated the development of automatic cephalometric landmark detection [38].",
    "In fact, the latest systematic reviews on this topic have shown an overall improvement in landmark identification when compared to the oldest [39][40][41]."
